<h3>Other Resources</h3>
<ul>
	<li><a href="http://www.childbirthconnection.org/" target="_blank">Child
	Birth Connection</a> <br />
	Childbirth Connection is a United States not-for-profit organization
	founded in 1918 as Maternity Center Association. Their mission is to
	improve the quality of maternity care through research, education,
	advocacy and policy. Childbirth Connection promotes safe, effective and
	satisfying evidence-based maternity care and provides valuable
	information for childbearing women and their families.<br />
	<br />
	</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.birthonlaborday.com/" target="_blank">Birth
	On A Labor Day</a><br />
	It is the website for BOLDBIRTH (Birth on Labor Day). Birth is a play
	based on over one hundred interviews New York playwright Karen Brody
	conducted with mothers across America who gave birth between 2000-2004.
	It tells the true stories of 8 women painting a portrait of how
	low-risk, educated women are giving birth in America today. Birth was
	performed in cities throughout the US on their Labor Day September 1.
	In 2006 Matrika organized a performance in Delhi. It is amazing how
	middle and upperclass Indian women's experiences in childbirth are
	similar to those in the US.<br />
	<br />
	</li>
	<li><a href="http://www.pbs.org/frontlineworld/stories/india701/"
		target="_blank">India: A second opinion; Frontline</a><br />
	This series of articles and videos gives an introduction into Ayurveda,
	from an outsider's point of view. Knowledge of Ayurveda is helpful in
	understanding many indigenous midwifery practices, even though Vaidyas
	do not conduct births. The center described in Coimbatore is beginning
	to offer Ayurvedic obstetrical services. They have found that their
	providing pre-natal care is not sufficient to guarantee a 'good birth'
	within other hospitals with obstetricians who practice bio-medicine.<br />
	<br />
